1: use pen and underline horizontally for important things, and add vertical lines at the start and end of *really* important things. so you end up with 2 tiers of highlights. 

underline only what *really* resonates and draw a star on the outer side of the page for easy retrieval.

2: avoid writing notes on the book itself since you'll prob lose/forget them. Opt for a digital note taker like reflect.notes where you can backlink subjects and compile notes. It syncs with Kindle
